RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 8500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIKINI NATION saved ground while being reserved off the pace, waited room nearing the quarter pole, slipped through entering the stretch, took the lead nearing the eighth pole and drew clear. VANDULIE was allowed to settle in stride, moved up four-wide nearing the quarter pole and finished strongly for second. NADITA saved ground while being unhurried, rallied strongly along the inside into the stretch, steadied running up on horses nearing the sixteenth, angled out and finished fast. MALICE TOWARD NONE vied with YOUGOTTAWANTIT for the lead from along the inside, drifted out nearing the three-sixteenths pole and weakened. YOUGOTTAWANTIT was bumped at the start by TICTALOODIE, then disputed the pace from along the outside top the stretch and tired. TICTALOODIE broke out to bump YOUGOTTAWANTIT, then dropped back and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Bikini Nation
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, inside, waited room 1/4, slipped thru, led 1/8, clear

ENTRY.NAME: Nadita
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, inside rally, steadied 1/16, finished fast

ENTRY.NAME: Malice Toward None
ENTRY.OWNER: One Horse Will Do Corporation and Leong Henry

ENTRY.NAME: Tictaloodie
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, bumped, dropped back, no factor

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 78. Starter Allowance Purse 9500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $3,500 OR LESS SINCE JULY 16, 2022 AND WHICH HAVE NOT WON A STARTER ALLOWANCE RACE AT EMERALD DOWNS IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winner s Of Two Races Since February 16, 2023 Allowed 3 lbs. (Maiden Races, Claiming Races And Starters Races For $3,200 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG MAMA THORNTON vied for the early lead from between horses, opened clear entering the stretch, responded to pressure and maintained a safe advantage. SQUARE FOOTAGE was allowed to settle in stride, rallied five-wide into the stretch and finished fast. RED PANTY NIGHT was reserved off the early pace, moved up along the outside on the turn, came six-wide into the stretch and finished strongly. MY MOONDANCER rushed up along the inside to vie for the lead for a half mile and weakened. FLYIN BY prompted the issue for a half mile while racing three-wide and tired. BETE ROUGE dropped back early and failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Big Mama Thornton
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied 2-wide, clear entering, maintained safe advantage

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR WASHINGTON BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD THREE YEAR OLDS, 121 LBS.; OLDER, 125 LBS. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AIN'T NO SISSY dueled with PEDAL TO THE METAL for the lead throughout and bested that one in a prolonged drive. PEDAL TO THE METAL dueled for the lead from the outside along the inside and just missed in a game effort. NIGHT TO REMEMBER was forwardly placed while racing three-wide and was gaining slightly late in a steady effort. FIRST ENDEAVOR was off a step slow, then settled in behind the leaders, angled out to be four-wide at the quarter pole but lacked a rally.

ENTRY.NAME: First Endeavor
ENTRY.COMMENT: off step slow, settled, 4-wide 1/4, lacked rally

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WESTERN RULE was forwardly placed early while racing three-wide, moved up to engage OLYMPIC LEGEND nearing the quarter pole, dueled with that one to the wire and prevailed narrowly in a stiff drive. OLYMPIC LEGEND set the pace while racing slightly off the rail, responded when challenged and just missed in a determined try. ABRAAJ MIRAGE saved ground while being close up early, angled out 3-wide nearing the three-sixteenths pole but lacked a rally. RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RESERVOIR was reserved off the early pace, moved up three-wide entering the quarter pole, found room between rivals entering the stretch, took the lead nearing the eighth pole and maintained a safe advantage. MS FLASHY HARBOR saved ground while being allowed to settle in stride, lacked room from the quarter pole to inside the three-sixteenths pole, angled out to follow the winner between horses, then angled in nearing the sixteenths pole and finished fast. MARY WALKER was forwardly placed while racing four-wide, was five-wide entering the stretch and finished strongly in a steady effort. CRAZY ABOUT YOU prompted the early pace while three-wide, came four-wide into the stretch and weakened. LADY ATTA TUDE vied for the lead from along the inside into the stretch and weakened. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Kent S. EMERALD DOWNS RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 87. Stakes Purse 50000. FOR THREE YEAR OLD FILLIES. (Maiden, Claiming and Starter races not considered) Starters to be named through the entry box by closing time of entries. Field size will be limited to 12 starters. RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALOHA BREEZE saved ground setting the pace in hand and drew off through the stretch to win as much the best while establishing a new stakes record. STEPUP saved ground chasing the winner, could not reach that one but finished well for second. JAMIES INHERITANCE was unhurried early, came four-wide into the stretch and was gaining slightly late. DADS ESTRELLA was reserved off the pace while racing three-wide but lacked a rally when asked. DRIVEWAY dropped back early while saving ground and failed to seriously threaten. MISS DYNAMIC prompted the issue from along the outside for three furlongs and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Stepup
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased, saved ground, no match, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Aloha Breeze
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace in hand, saved ground, drew off, easily

ENTRY.NAME: Driveway
ENTRY.COMMENT: dropped back, saved ground, no threat

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 9 6F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE APRIL 1, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TUMAC MOUNTAIN vied for the lead from between horses while three-wide, opened a clear lead entering the stretch and maintained a safe advantage. SENOR FABULOSO saved ground while being unhurried, swung out to come five-wide into the stretch and finished fast. MILEYS BLUECAT vied for the early lead from along the inside, checked in tight nearing the five-sixteenths pole, angled out to come four-wide into the stretch and was gaining late. UNION BLISS hesitated and then hopped at the start to get away well behind the field, rallied six-wide into the stretch but was unable to recover the lost ground. HULA KING prompted the issue while racing four-wide and weakened. SIERRA MELODY vied for the early lead while racing two-wide and tired. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE START AND ALSO THE INCIDENT NEARING THE FIVE-SIXTEENTHS POLE BUT AFTER VIEWING THE FILMS MADE NO CHANGE IN THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, checked 5/16, angled out 4-wide entering, mild rally
